    "subject": "Implement borderless window mode",
    "description": "At least on windows, a borderless window mode would allow for faster, less cumbersome switching between windows, doing some work in other windows while ET:L stays temporarily in the background.\r\n\r\nW:ET in fullscreen allows alt-tabbing, but stays on top, rendering the functionality of alt+tab useless. In windowed mode, the window borders, especially the top one of > 20 px makes it waste usable space and prevents rendering in a native resolution, without losing the display of the bottom of the window.\r\n\r\nIn ET:L alt-tabbing in fullscreen does work, minimizing the ET:L window, which makes it usable. However, a borderless window mode as an alternative to the other two mentioned modes would provide an additional useful rendering mode. With borderless window mode switching windows is instant, in contrast to the minimization and restoration and would thus provide additional benefit.\r\n\r\n\r\nOn IRC, the SDL flag SDL_NOFRAME was mentioned, which would remove borders all-together. However, a third mode additionally to fullscreen and windowed would be desired, as there are use-cases for all three of them.",
